In this article, President Joe Biden reflects on the significance of Mother's Day and honors the mothers and mother figures in our lives. He acknowledges the lessons he learned from his own mother and praises his wife, First Lady Jill Biden, for her love and support. The President highlights the important role that mothers play in society, from nurturing children to driving innovation and leading in various fields. He discusses the efforts of his administration to support mothers, such as providing childcare assistance, expanding the Child Tax Credit, and enacting laws to protect pregnant workers and nursing parents. Vice President Kamala Harris is also mentioned for her work in improving maternal health and ensuring fair treatment for pregnant women and mothers. The President encourages Americans to express their love and gratitude to mothers and calls for appropriate observance of Mother's Day.